            "id": "devotion",
            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EDavid%20tells%20us%20three%20things%20we%20must%20do%20to%20emerge%20victorious%20from%20troubles.%20First%2C%20he%20tells%20us%20to%20praise%20the%20Lord%20(Psalm%2034%3A1).%20When%20we%20bless%20the%20Lord%20for%20all%20His%20benefits%2C%20boast%20in%20the%20Lord%20concerning%20His%20attributes%2C%20and%20exalt%20Him%20for%20His%20goodness%2C%20we%20are%20focusing%20on%20Him%20instead%20of%20our%20troubles.%20How%20easy%20it%20is%2C%20though%2C%20to%20let%20trouble%20take%20over%20our%20thinking%20to%20the%20point%20that%20we%20forget%20how%20great%20God%20is!%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ESecond%2C%20David%20tells%20us%20to%20seek%20the%20Lord%20(v.%204%20KJV).%20To%20seek%20means%20%22to%20inquire%20diligently%2C%22%20or%20%22to%20reach%20a%20place%20of%20desperation.%22%20David%20knew%20this%20kind%20of%20desperate%20crying%20out%20to%20God%20and%20the%20results%20it%20brought%3A%20%22This%20poor%20man%20cried%2C%20and%20the%20Lord%20heard%20him%2C%20and%20saved%20him%20out%20of%20all%20his%20troubles%22%20(v.%206%20KJV).%20Hezekiah%20turned%20his%20face%20to%20the%20wall%2C%20Moses%20stretched%20out%20his%20rod%2C%20Peter%20put%20on%20his%20sandals%20.%20.%20.%20and%20God%20delivered%20from%20sickness%2C%20danger%2C%20and%20imprisonment!%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EFinally%2C%20David%20said%20to%20reverence%20the%20Lord%20(v.%209).%20We%20must%20examine%20every%20area%20of%20our%20lives%20to%20be%20certain%20our%20giving%2C%20our%20words%2C%20and%20our%20relationships%20are%20in%20order.%20In%20this%20way%2C%20we%20honor%20God.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EWhen%20we%20praise%20the%20Lord%2C%20seek%20the%20Lord%2C%20and%20reverence%20the%20Lord%2C%20we%20will%20be%20delivered%20from%20all%20our%20troubles!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
